text.tspan: Training computation vs. parameters in notable AI systems, by
Computation is measured in total petaFLOP, which is 10ยนโต floating-point operations estimated from AI literature, albeit with
some uncertainty. Parameters are variables in an AI system whose values are adjusted during training to establish how input
data gets transformed into the desired output.
Note: Each domain's training data has a specific unit; for example, for vision it is images and for language it is words. This means
systems can only be compared directly within the same domain.
